# AI System Principles

- Prioritize reliability, grounding, and observability.
- Minimize hallucinations.
- Keep prompts structured and deterministic.
- Keep orchestration explicit and understandable.
- Avoid uncontrolled autonomous loops.
- Include source attribution when applicable.
- Log important workflow steps.

# Retrieval-Augmented Generation

- Separate ingestion, chunking, embedding, retrieval, and generation.
- Store metadata alongside chunks.
- Retrieve only relevant context.
- Use reasonable chunk overlap.
- Return source references when applicable.
- If context is insufficient, avoid unsupported claims.

# Agentic Workflow Guidelines

- Keep responsibilities narrow and well-defined.
- Prefer deterministic flows before autonomous behavior.
- Make state transitions explicit.
- Add retry/error handling for tool calls.
- Avoid unnecessary multi-agent complexity.
- Design systems to be easy to debug and test.

# API Integration

- Use environment variables for secrets.
- Keep API calls wrapped in reusable functions.
- Avoid hardcoding credentials.
- Handle API failures gracefully.